column5: i got mine in unit 50 as well as my Dad
I got mine for WMU 60, and my Party fell apart...again So I got the tag and no were to get in and hunt grrrrrrr....  I'll apply elsewere next year
Got lucky this year antlerless for me 1st one ever but they're hard as hell to come by in unit 42.

I know it,s a bit of a drive there Cookslav,but if you have bow and willing to travel,I be willing to put you on a stand for a day. Heck even have a BBQ at the end of the day.     Thats what it,s all about. Nature.LOL
3 of us here got our tags in the mail last night for the archury season.All anterless. Cant wait. Anyone else get thiers?
...but do you know where there are any deer ??????
Got mine this morning! First time getting one, however I've only applied 3 times.  I hunt in Zone 48.

Ok MisMan I wanna see pics of venison burgers come November---also you have to pose with the arrow that got it for qualification.  Here's a fat one my boy shot---1 round---1 jump----1 batch of canned venison for the painter  Bushart
Got mine, Wezzz got to post pictures if lucky.
Yup I got my regular one and a extra one!!
got mine yesterday wmu 47
Guddun..  Hope you do well dude.  Watch out for them mangy dogs though!!

I got mine, and my extra tag too.. I can't wait to get out in the woods again, and have some peace and quiet. I am still waiting for my big buck from last year to get out of my taxidermists hands, hopefully soon.
This is the first year I havent got a doe tag for the rifle hunt. Buck only tag for me, but other camp members have doe tags so life is good. Not lucky in the moose draw either. CALF !!!

Wizeninhymer  The land owner is now in the new house.I get daily reports, as he also works in the plant.    I dont think the rifle hunt/control hunt ones are out yet????????????????? Just the archury tags.
I bought a big knife.
Yes the rifle ones are the same time as the archery tags. The controlled shotgun hasnt happend yet I dont think. My brother got a doe archery for 76
Cool thanks. 76 here aswell. Phelpston. Applied for the control aswell. Hope my pop gets his doe tag. That will be the second week hunt for me and my bro and pop.
Recieved my antlerless for WMU 77 yesturday also. Going to try to get an extra tag now.
Thats yer pops place Doug? Maybe do some swap hunts this season?
Got my antlerless tag today. WMU 37.
Man , am I the only one that didnt get a doe tag ? what a rip
Seeing this post and getting an email from my dad I figured mine would be here as well.  It was in the mailbox.  43B for me.  I'll be using it in muzzleloader season in December though.

The only way we up here in WMU 13 don't get an antlerless tag is if we do not apply, but it is a flippin' huge management area compared to southern Ontario, with the option to purchase more deer tags, antlered only I believe. I do not buy the extra tags so I am not that sure of what I just said. 3 guys, 3 deer, lots of meat. At least enough for us. Now, if I can only get out hunting. Work, and life, has been an issue the last couple of years
Still snowing up there Tom? LOL

We finally got expected summer weather last week, for about 4 days. I ain't complaining though, I hate the heat wave weather. Most times this summer the highs have been in the 18-22C range, with minimal precipitation until until the last 3 weeks. Then the skies have opened up on us at times. We do need the rain though, just people lament at the rain ruining their weekends, I just fished through it a couple of times, And, the winds have been a pain, just a different year up here for us weather wise.
I guess thats one of the benefits of hunting down here at home. Antlerless tags are not hard to come by.  I got mine and my additional tag in the mail last night - WMU 87.  35 days to go!!!!!
Sure, if you like having cold feet while you watch the squirrels play all day.
